A former governor of Lagos State and All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential aspirant, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has expressed high confidence in winning the party ticket and proceeding to clinch the exalted position of the president of the Federal Republic of Nigeria in 2023. Tinubu who was in Kaduna to canvass the support of the delegates on Thursday, 6th May 2023 declared that he does not know where other aspirants are running to but for him, he is running to the villa. The former governor urged the party delegates in Kaduna to support his presidential struggle for 2023, saying, “follow the man who knows the road.” -Advertisement- He declared: “Honestly speaking I don’t know where they are running to but for me, I am running to the villa. That’s where I want to be in 2023 In sha Allah. “I will also advise you to follow me because I know the road to the villa.” Tinubu reminded the delegates, “Kaduna, you have been very consistent. I believe you will follow me. Follow the man who knows the road. He urged the party delegates in Kaduna to support his Presidential struggle for 2023, saying, “follow the man who knows the road.” Tinubu who met the delegates, led by Governor Nasir El-Rufai at the Murtala Square said that he was aware that there are other presidential aspirants in the party seeking the office. POLL “But honestly speaking I don’t know where they are running to but for me, I am running to the villa. That’s where I want to be in 2023 In shaa Allah. “I will also advise you to follow me because I know the road to the villa.” He repeated.